events.description:
DevFest Florida late bird tickets are on sale now, but not after today, Halloween!!! 

Ttickets are $75 which gets you access to:

• all of the speaker sessions,

• lunch, snacks, and refreshments,

• a conference t-shirt,

events.name: Google CloudNext - Extended '17
events.description:
Join the Central Florida Google Developer Group for Cloud Tech CodeLabs, Developer networking event, and keynote presentations from Google CloudNext '17. Please RSVP because we will be providing food & beverages to all attendees .

Bring your laptop to work on the code labs.   Prior to the event, review the codelabs at google.qwiklabs.com

• 10:00 am - 10:30 am Registration, Introductions and Code Lab Setups

• 10:30 am - 12:00 noon Stream Opening Keynote from March 8th

Hear from Diane Greene, SVP of Google Cloud; Sundar Pichai, CEO of Google; Eric Schmidt, Chairman of Alphabet and Fei-Fei Li, Chief Scientist for Google Cloud Machine Learning and AI and Professor of Computer Science at Stanford. Our lineup of executives will discuss what Google Cloud offers today and discuss Google Cloud's vision for the future. Attendees will also hear how Google customers and partners are embracing the cloud in new and innovative ways.

• 12:00 noon - 1:30 pm  - Streamling Live Keynote from March 10th and LUNCH

Fei Fei Li - Chief Scientist, Cloud AI & ML, Google Cloud, Vint Cerf -VP and Chief Internet Evangelist, Google,  Sam Ramji - VP, Product Development, Compute & Developer Services, Google Cloud

CODE LABS

• 1:30 - 2:00 Detect Objects, Faces and Landmarks in Images with the Cloud Vision API

• 2:00 - 3:00 Build a Node.js Web App using the Google Cloud Platform

• 3:00 - 3:30 snack break, networking, self-paced code labs

• 3:30 - 4:00 Entity and Sentiment Analysis with the Natural Language API

NOTE:  As a member of this Meetup group, you are eligible to apply for a 50% discount to attend the live event March 8 - 10th in San Francisco in person !

https://goo.gl/Aeaxxl 

#GoogleNext17 #GDGCentralFlorida #extended

events.description:
Google's I/O event is their annual developer event. If you can't make it to Mountain View but want to enjoy all the news, code labs and excitement this event is for you! events.description:

YOU MUST REGISTER & PAY FOR THIS MEETUP - We have an early bird discount code for this meetup group that expires soon  - Use code = CENTRAL-FL-GDG to get 20% off your registration

DevFest Florida 2017 is a combined DevFest being organized by three Google Developer Groups in the central Florida area: Space Coast, Central Florida, and Sun Coast. These GDG chapters support the Orlando, Tampa, and Melbourne areas of central Florida. See https://devfestflorida.org/ for updates because we are expecting some exciting speakers this year! 

DevFest Florida is the biggest Google tech conference in Florida this year. BUT it's also so much more! It is all about Android, Web, Cloud, AI, AR/VR, IoT and more!

We're attracting diverse developers from around the globe to speak about the most exciting technologies that you are working with or want to. The idea behind DevFest Florida is to bring top talent to Florida,  and to help developers, designers create relationships with each other & organizations.

events.name: Cloud Study Jam
events.description:
== What is a Google Cloud Study Jam? ==

Study Jams are community-run study groups. The objective of Study Jams is to raise the technical proficiency of our community members through well defined projects, labs and technical knowledge sharing.

== How does it benefits me? ==

+ Learn how to set up development and production environments in the Cloud.
+ Learn the fundamentals of the Google Cloud Platform, how to run containers on it and how to use the platform for data engineering.
+ Learn how Docker and Kubernetes work, or learn how to process Big Data in the Cloud.
+ Get access to Qwiklabs.com, a Google training tool, FREE of charge. **NOTE** codes provided are tied to the event date (Feb. 22) and will ONLY be available to those present at the event.
+ Get Google-hosted badges for your online profiles, to show potential employers what you know about Cloud computing.

== How long does it takes? ==

Approximately 10 hours. During this meetup we will provide you with the links and tokens require to complete the labs. We'll also work as group to complete the first few labs during the event.
We'll create a Cloud Study Jam Slack channel to help everyone collaborate on the labs following the event.

== What do you need? ==

- Bring your laptop and charger. We'll work on the labs together. Mac/PC is ok. We only need a browser and internet connectivity.
- JOIN channel #cloudstudyjam on GDG Central Florida Slack workspace get invite here https://gdgcf.herokuapp.com

== About venue and parking ==

PowerDMS is located in the third floor of the Exchange building, entrance on Pine Street. Close to Church Street Train Station.
The building is across the street from public and private parking.

events.name: Exploring TypeScript+NodeJS and Google ARCore
events.description:
Increasing NodeJS productivity using TypeScript: Front-end Angular developers enjoy the TypeScript programming language to help reduce errors, increase productivity, implement true class structures, and to leverage the benefits of static compilation. NodeJS developers can leverage TypeScript on the server side too. During this session, our friend Danny Mayer will explore the benefits of building applications using TypeScript, Angular, and ExpressJS. You don't want to miss this insightful talk! </p>

Getting Started with Google ARCore: In the future, imagine using an AR app to plan and layout furniture in a space. Imagine how biology students might use an AR app to explore 3D cell structures or processes. What would it be like to make the real world a level for your next game? All of these scenarios become possible with Google ARCore. In this talk, we'll walk through the process of building an ARCore app on Android.</p>

events.description:
Computer vision continues to be one of the most exciting sensors you can incorporate in your IoT project. In this workshop, Michael Rosario will survey a few tools to leverage computer vision in your next DIY Raspberry Pi project from simple robotics to augmented reality. We’ll explore open source projects like SimpleCV for python. We'll review using NodeJs for cloud integrations with Google Cloud Vision. events.name: Road To DevFest: An Evening of Angular
events.description:
This event is part of the Road To DevFest Tour
DevFest Florida tickets are available at
https://devfestflorida-orlando.eventbrite.com

Join us for an exciting evening of talks about new ways to build applications with Angular.

Talks

What's New in Angular
Stephen Fluin / Developer Advocate at Google

This talk will provide an update about the latest and greatest from the
Angular team in terms of pushing the productivity and efficacy of
developers all over the world. Learn about the latest releases, features,
and capabilities with a live coding demo, and get a sneak peak at where
Angular is headed in the future.

=====

Composing Accessible UIs with Angular Material Components
Michael Prentice / Software Consultant Angular Team

Angular Material provides core components and a Component Dev Kit. However, it's up to developers to integrate the various core components when creating an application. The docs are focused on individual components (behaviors, APIs, etc). In this talk, we'll dig deep into the code with concrete, real-world examples of how to compose a quality, accessible user experience with Angular Material.

=====

Making Angular Test Automation Awesome with Jest Testing Framework
Thomas Bottonari / Lead front-end developer at LSQ.com

Change is a constant in software development. As Angular developers, how do we create effective test automation solutions to maximize quality in our code? How do we integrate this automation into our CI/CD processes? Thomas Bottonari, lead front-end developer at LSQ financial, will share motivations, lessons learned and implementation tips for using Facebook Jest testing framework with Angular.

AGENDA

events.description:
This event is part of the Road To DevFest Tour DevFest Florida tickets are available at

Secrets To Using Social Media To Create Tech Gig Opportunities
with @msbrandymorgan

Social media expert, developer, and designer, Brandy Morgan, will share her insights to grow your personal brand and connect with great client opportunities in technology using social media. Whether you work in consulting, you're leading a startup or you're looking for your next dream job, this talk is for you. Make sure to follow Brandy on Twitter at @msbrandymorgan. We're also looking forward to learning about Brandy's latest startup, CreatorsCode.co. We can't wait to share the story at our next Google developers meetup!

====

VueJs and Google FireStore

As web developers, we love JavaScript. It gives us the ability to express high impact applications with simplicity. Looking for a scalable platform for building your next killer application? In this meetup, we’ll explore building web apps with Vue.js and Google Cloud Firestore using real application examples. Cloud FireStore provides all the important platform tools for your startup or application: authentication, real-time database, security, analytics, and data query. It’s a great platform to keep you focused on your application. (not infrastructure)

We also want to thank TekSystems for providing beer and pizza for our meeting. Really appreciate their support of the Orlando tech community.
